00:28.000 --> 00:30.000
And that is error boundaries.

00:30.000 --> 00:40.000
So, what happens if, let's say, our past lazy.jsx had an error with its API request and it was an uncaught error,

00:40.000 --> 00:43.000
it would just bubble up to the top of the app and crash the app, right?

00:43.000 --> 00:46.000
As you've seen several times happen in our app where it just says, like,

00:46.000 --> 00:49.000
I give up, the whole thing crashed, right?

00:49.000 --> 00:53.000
There's a thing called error boundaries that allow you to, like, catch those errors

00:53.000 --> 00:59.000
and, like, you know, prevent it from crashing your app.

00:59.000 --> 01:01.000
And you can only do it with class components.

01:01.000 --> 01:05.000
